<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>redkb – Devops</title><link>/tags/devops/</link><description>Recent content in Devops on redkb</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 04 Jul 2026 03:09:01 -0400</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="/tags/devops/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>gh CLI</title><link>/docs/devops/github/gh-cli/</link><pubDate>Sat, 04 Jul 2026 03:09:01 -0400</pubDate><guid>/docs/devops/github/gh-cli/</guid><description>
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href="https://cli.github.com"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Github CLI&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is a terminal interface for interacting with Github repositories. You can use it within a pipeline/action to simplify interactions with your repositories, such as creating and merging pull requests, triggering pipelines, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Authenticating with Github CLI&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="authenticating-with-github-cli"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#authenticating-with-github-cli" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you try to run a pipeline manually using the &lt;code&gt;gh&lt;/code&gt; CLI, but you are not signed in or do not have admin privileges, you will see an error like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;could not create workflow dispatch event: HTTP 403: Must have admin rights to Repository.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To fix this, use a &lt;a href="https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure/managing-your-personal-access-tokens"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Personal Access Token (PAT)&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with the following permissions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actions: Read and write&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contents: Read and write&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Workflows: Read and write&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can also optionally add the below to enable more functionality via the &lt;code&gt;gh&lt;/code&gt; CLI:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Code scanning alerts: Read only&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deployments: Read and write (to manage Github Pages deployments)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Issues: Read and write (to manage issues from the CLI)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pages: Read and write (for managing Pages deployments)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pull requests: Read and write (to manage PRs from the CLI)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then, run &lt;code&gt;gh auth login&lt;/code&gt; to start the interactive login process. If you are not able to do the interactive method, export your token with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;GH_TOKEN&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;&amp;lt;your-gh-PAT&amp;gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then, run your &lt;code&gt;gh&lt;/code&gt; commands; they will use the &lt;code&gt;$GH_TOKEN&lt;/code&gt; environment variable automatically. For example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;gh workflow run Some&lt;span class="se"&gt;\ &lt;/span&gt;pipeline&lt;span class="se"&gt;\ &lt;/span&gt;name --ref feat/branch-to-run-on&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Using the Github CLI to trigger releases&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="using-the-github-cli-to-trigger-releases"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#using-the-github-cli-to-trigger-releases" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;When developing a pipeline, you may need to trigger it in a way the Github webUI doesn&amp;rsquo;t allow. For example, if you create a brand new pipeline, or if you add a &lt;code&gt;workflow_dispatch&lt;/code&gt; and have not merged the branch with this change yet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can use the &lt;a href="https://cli.github.com"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Github CLI&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to trigger a pipeline from a specific branch, in ways that the Github webUI doesn&amp;rsquo;t allow. For example, if the &lt;a href="../.github/workflows/hugo-release.yml"&gt;&lt;code&gt;hugo-release.yml&lt;/code&gt; pipeline&lt;/a&gt; did not have a &lt;code&gt;workflow_dispatch&lt;/code&gt; on the &lt;code&gt;main&lt;/code&gt; branch, but you added one in a branch named &lt;code&gt;feat/manual-trigger-release&lt;/code&gt;, you can test that trigger before merging the changes into &lt;code&gt;main&lt;/code&gt;. If you went to this pipeline in the webUI, you would see there is no manual trigger button. This is because the &lt;code&gt;workflow_dispatch&lt;/code&gt; change does not exist on the &lt;code&gt;main&lt;/code&gt; branch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can trigger the pipeline manually with the &lt;code&gt;gh&lt;/code&gt; CLI like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;gh workflow run hugo-release.yml --ref feat/manual-trigger-release&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If a &lt;code&gt;workflow_dispatch&lt;/code&gt; has inputs, you can pass them with &lt;code&gt;-f&lt;/code&gt;, like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;gh workflow run pipeline-filename.yml &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; --ref feat/manual-trigger-release &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; -f input-one&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="se"&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; -f input-two&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;some-value&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Tips &amp; Tricks</title><link>/docs/devops/github/tips-tricks/</link><pubDate>Sat, 04 Jul 2026 03:08:07 -0400</pubDate><guid>/docs/devops/github/tips-tricks/</guid><description>
&lt;h2&gt;Test trigger with empty commit&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="test-trigger-with-empty-commit"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#test-trigger-with-empty-commit" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;For fully automatic pipelines, i.e. ones that run on PR open or merge, you can trigger the behavior by adding a &lt;code&gt;push&lt;/code&gt; to your branch, then pushing an empty commit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For example, in the &lt;a href="../.github/workflows/hugo-release.yml"&gt;&lt;code&gt;hugo-release.yml&lt;/code&gt; pipeline&lt;/a&gt;, the pipeline watches for changes to &lt;code&gt;.version&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;.bumpversion.toml&lt;/code&gt; on pull requests that are merged to the &lt;code&gt;main&lt;/code&gt; branch:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nn"&gt;---&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="l"&gt;Hugo release&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;on&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;push&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;branches&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;- &lt;span class="l"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;paths&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;- &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;.version&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;- &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;.bumpversion.toml&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To test this automatic trigger from your branch, you can add the current branch name, i.e. &lt;code&gt;feat/something-automatic&lt;/code&gt;, disable path filtering, and push an empty commit:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;---
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;name: Hugo release
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;on:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; push:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; branches:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; - main
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;## Watch the current branch, in addition to main.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Remove this when you&amp;#39;re done testing, before&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;# merging back into main&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; - feat/something-automatic
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;## Temporarily disable path watching&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;# paths:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;# - &amp;#34;.version&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;# - &amp;#34;.bumpversion.toml&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Commit these changes, push them, then create and push an empty commit to trigger it:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-code-block hx:relative hx:mt-6 hx:first:mt-0 hx:group/code"&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="l"&gt;git commit --allow-empty -m &amp;#34;chore: test workflow trigger&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="l"&gt;git push&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="hextra-code-copy-btn-container hx:transition hx:group-hover/code:opacity-100 hx:flex hx:gap-1 hx:absolute hx:m-[11px] hx:right-0 hx:top-0"&gt;
&lt;button
class="hextra-code-copy-btn hx:group/copybtn hx:cursor-pointer hx:transition-all hx:active:opacity-50 hx:bg-primary-700/5 hx:border hx:border-black/5 hx:text-gray-600 hx:hover:text-gray-900 hx:rounded-md hx:p-1.5 hx:dark:bg-primary-300/10 hx:dark:border-white/10 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50"
title="Copy code"
aria-label="Copy code"
data-copied-label="Copied!"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-copy-icon hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:hidden hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hextra-success-icon hx:hidden hx:group-[.copied]/copybtn:block hx:pointer-events-none hx:h-4 hx:w-4"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:flex-col hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-4 hx:px-4 hx:border-gray-200 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-purple-200 hx:bg-purple-100 hx:text-purple-900 hx:dark:border-purple-200/30 hx:dark:bg-purple-900/30 hx:dark:text-purple-200"&gt;
&lt;p class="hx:flex hx:items-center hx:font-medium"&gt;&lt;svg height=16px class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle hx:mr-2" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;Important&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Don&amp;rsquo;t forget to put your triggers back to normal after a successful test. Remove the branch and uncomment any filtering rules that should run on &lt;code&gt;main&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Devops</title><link>/docs/devops/</link><pubDate>Sat, 04 Jul 2026 03:06:41 -0400</pubDate><guid>/docs/devops/</guid><description>
&lt;p&gt;Developer Operations (DevOps) is the integration and automation of software development and IT operations. It is primarily aimed at shortening the development process and improving the development lifecycle. The field has continued to evolve over the years, with sub-specializations such as Platform Engineering (maintaining the &amp;ldquo;platform&amp;rdquo; developers build on top of), Site Reliability Engineering (building the infrastructure for monitoring and alerting), Finance Operations (automating financial aspects of software development), Development Security Operations (integrating security steps into the development process), Release Engineering (building &amp;amp; maintaining the processes &amp;amp; automations around releasing software versions) &amp;amp; more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As software development became more complex and moved more towards the cloud, a niche formed between the actual software development, and everything that comes after, including builds &amp;amp; releases, security, and cloud deployment. The descriptions of each title above are not universal; companies often post positions using the DevOps branch titles interchangeably, and there are many responsibilities shared between the different titles. The specializations above do not necessarily mean that is &lt;em&gt;all&lt;/em&gt; an engineer will handle, but each title is focused on a different aspect of the overarching &amp;ldquo;DevOps&amp;rdquo; umbrella.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Sections&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="sections"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#sections" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;table&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Section&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/thead&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="./github/"&gt;Github&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Documentation for Github Actions &amp;amp; reusable workflows.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</description></item><item><title>Github CI/CD</title><link>/docs/devops/github/</link><pubDate>Sat, 04 Jul 2026 03:06:32 -0400</pubDate><guid>/docs/devops/github/</guid><description>
&lt;p&gt;Github&amp;rsquo;s CI/CD platform is broken into 2 units: &lt;a href="https://docs.github.com/en/actions"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Github Actions&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://docs.github.com/en/actions/how-tos/reuse-automations/reuse-workflows"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;reusable workflows&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Describing workflows and actions makes them sound like the same thing (or very similar), and to an extent they are. I will let Github&amp;rsquo;s documentation explain this in-depth, but the short version is that a reusable workflow is a set of &amp;ldquo;jobs&amp;rdquo; to automate code actions like linting, building, releasing, etc, and they can be chained together. An action (or &amp;ldquo;reusable component&amp;rdquo;) is like a CI/CD component package that a workflow can call to handle a very specific step, like &lt;a href="https://github.com/actions/checkout"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;cloning a repository&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href="https://github.com/actions/setup-node"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;installing Node.js&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (or other languages).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Official Actions are stored in the &lt;a href="https://github.com/actions"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Github Actions repository&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but anyone can create an action in their own repository. The Github Actions platform is strict about where actions and workflows must live; you cannot call an action or workflow from a path outside of &lt;code&gt;.github/&lt;/code&gt;. This means that whether your reusable actions or workflows are stored in the repo that calls them, or a centralized repository with all of your pipeline components, they must exist under a specific path:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;.github/workflows/&lt;/code&gt; for reusable workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;.github/actions/&lt;/code&gt; for reusable components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are some other differences between actions and workflows. Actions do not use a &lt;code&gt;jobs:&lt;/code&gt; section, meaning you can&amp;rsquo;t create a multi-stage actions (you would have to use a workflow for that). Additionally, actions cannot inherit or use secrets, where workflows can. This design is intentional; the idea is that a workflow is made up of a series of action calls, while each action handles 1 very specific task/process. A reddit user named &lt;code&gt;/u/queen-adreena&lt;/code&gt; summed it up perfectly: &lt;a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/github/comments/17sbywi/what_is_a_github_workflow_and_how_does_it_differ/"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&amp;ldquo;An action is a song. A workflows is a playlist&amp;rdquo;&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Github provides a &lt;a href="https://github.com/actions/reusable-workflows"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;repository of reusable workflows&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that help with the development of action components.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>